cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.DL (Digital Libraries) sub-category as it deals with the analysis of ranking systems and their indicators, which are often based on digital data and information. It also involves the comparison of different ranking systems, which requires the use of digital tools and techniques. 

The paper could also belong to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category as it involves the retrieval and analysis of information from different ranking systems. 

The cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper discusses the value and limits of world university rankings, which have implications for society and the role of universities in it. 

The cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Development) sub-categories are less likely but still possible as the paper involves the analysis of data and the use of software tools to compare different ranking systems.
